stylometry: A regression equation is the formula for a line. It tells you the independent variables and how they relate to the dependent variable. In a simple linear regression, there is only one independent variable, and with a multiple regression, there are several (or more than one) independent variable. You can use a regression equation to determine whether or not your variables correlate with one another. An example of this would be advertisements and selling apartments. Do these two variables correlate? Or in other words, do advertisements have an affect on how many apartments you sell?
